title: Funeral held for British-Israeli woman who died after West Bank attack that killed daughters
description: The funeral of British-Israeli woman Lucy Dee has been held after she was killed alongside her daughters in an attack in the West Bank.

title: World economy entering 'perilous phase' with UK to perform worst in G7 this year
description: The IMF, which is holding its spring meetings in Washington this week, downgraded its outlook for global growth and said its medium term forecast for economic output was now at the weakest level since the fund began publishing these forecasts in 1990.

title: French strikes disrupt power supply and nuclear reactor maintenance
description: Maintenance at nine French nuclear reactors was disrupted due to the strike against the government's planned pension reforms.

title: Chinese firm enters AI arms race with ChatGPT-like model
description: Alibaba has become the latest Chinese technology giant to unveil its own ChatGPT-like AI model.

title: Germany to shut final three nuclear power plants
description: Germany is on course to shut down its three remaining nuclear power plants on Saturday.

title: Venus has more volcanoes than we thought - and this map shows where they are
description: Venus has long been known as a home to plenty of volcanoes - but not quite this many.

title: Taiwanese rush to buy anti-Xi Jinping badge of Winnie the Pooh being punched
description: People in Taiwan are rushing to buy anti-Xi Jinping badges being worn by their air force pilots.

title: AI generated newsreader debuts in Kuwait
description: An AI generated newsreader has been revealed by a media outlet in Kuwait.

title: Iran installs cameras in public places to identify unveiled women
description: Iranian authorities are installing cameras in public places to identify and penalise unveiled women in an attempt to rein in the increasing numbers who are defying the country's strict dress rules.

title: US and Philippines holding biggest combat drills in decades after China-Taiwan standoff
description: The US and the Philippines are holding their largest combat drills in decades after China conducted mock air and sea attacks off the coast of Taiwan.
